  "notes": "Cornish (Kernewek). Revived language; last native speaker died 1777. Revival since early 20th c.; ~3,000 speakers (est. 2020). Three main revival orthographies: Kernewek Standard, Kernewek Unys, Spellyans. This spec follows revived Kernewek Standard pronunciation. Refs: George (1993), Brown (2001).",
